commentary_data: Both RR and Punjab are coming into this game on the back of convincing wins. The narratives don't spark much of an excitement though. It is the title drought for both units that would be pushing them to do better than before. RR won in 2008 and made it to the finale in 2022 only to be outdone by the Gujarat unit. Punjab have had hapless and reckless years ever since the inception of the IPL. They came close in 2014 but post that the same story has been told on a loop.
I0$ informs -- Greetings from Guwahati. It rained from midnight till about 4:00 in the morning. But the weather looks fine now.

I0$ Their top 3. The artillery at the top fired the opponents down. Almost sealed the fate in the first half. Their bowlers also chipped in to make it an all-round effort. Seems this is an extension of 2022!

I0$ Their top order also batted impressively. Arshdeep's new ball exploits also sowed the seeds of the win against KKR. D/L came into play and bridged the gap. Barring Russell's threatening cameo, Punjab didn't come under much pressure.
Gokul adds, "Lots of pink in the stands and some PBKS jerseys, as expected. But the CSK yellow and jerseys with No.7 on the back also seen at the Barsapara stadium."

The dimensions of the ground are unique. The square boundaries vary from one another. The pitch looks a belter. Little live grass and there is some dryness on the wicket. Players who can swing the ball like Boult can be effective.

What both should guard against? RR can be found culprit of an overdependence on their top-order. And Punjab have a definite amount of reliance on Arshdeep. Sam Curran unlike the last game has to do a better job with the new and old ball.
The venue is the Barsapara Stadium. It is expected to rain runs. Expect a run feast. In that case the experience in the bowling line up of RR will definitely come in handy.

Tremendous start. It is a group which is pretty familiar with each other. I suppose we have continued with the form from the last year. We appreciate it is a new year and a new season. New personnel. New faces. But the messages and the consistency around the change room has been the same. We look to back each other. My role is to pick uo early wickets with the new ball.

I have been given more responsibility, I used to bat at 6 in the domestics, where I was mainly used as a finisher. But here we have players like Sam Curran and Raza, that's the reason I have been pushed up, it's a chance to play more sensibly and contribute to the team. My role changed with the game. In the last game I needed to carry forward the momentum created by Bhanuka (Rajapaksha). My role was to score at a good rate which I did and made some 25 odd runs in quick time. My first time over here, I watched the India-South Africa game, it was a high-scoring game. So I think the crowd here in Guwahati will enjoy watching the match.

We would like to bowl here. Expecting some dew. We will use the oppurtunity to bowl first. It is a great thought by the franchise. Loving it here. The players have gotten used to the conditions. We are going in with the same side. Very happy to see them grow. Jaiswal and Parag have grown a lot learning from the experienced guys.

We all know the dew comes. We also wanted to bowl first. It is alright. We are used to it. Let's go day by day. Not putting too much on pressure on myself. The process matters the most. Same eleven from the last game. RR are a very good side. They are playing good cricket. We want to give our best.
(Playing XI): Yashasvi Jaiswal, Jos Buttler, Sanju Samson(w/c), Devdutt Padikkal, Riyan Parag, Shimron Hetmyer, Jason Holder, Ravichandran Ashwin, Trent Boult, KM Asif, Yuzvendra Chahal
(Playing XI): Shikhar Dhawan(c), Prabhsimran Singh, Bhanuka Rajapaksa, Jitesh Sharma(w), Shahrukh Khan, Sam Curran, Sikandar Raza, Nathan Ellis, Harpreet Brar, Rahul Chahar, Arshdeep Singh
Dhruv Jurel, Akash Vasisht, Murugan Ashwin, Kuldip Yadav, Donavon Ferreira
Rishi Dhawan, Atharva Taide, Harpreet Singh Bhatia, Matthew Short, Mohit Rathee
All in readiness. Punjab would eye another explosive start. Boult has the ball in his hands.

Boult to Prabhsimran, 1 run, looks to go hard at one outside off and stabs the ball down into the off-side to find the man at point mopping it up. They get a single. Looked to hit it too hard and hence couldn't time it
Boult to Dhawan, , slips one down leg, the batter misses the tuck and the keeper fumbles a little to give away an extra run. That slanted into the batter
Boult to Prabhsimran, no run, looks to drive and gets an inside edge. The man at square leg stops it with a dive
Boult to Prabhsimran, , and doesn't take too long for Prabhsimran to get moving. That was slanted across fuller and outside off, Prabhsimran gets under it and slams it over cover. Well timed
Boult to Prabhsimran, no run, looks to go hard at one outside off and chops the ball down to the man at slip. That was slanted across on a length outside off
Boult to Prabhsimran, no run, back of a length delivery, little kick on it and Prabhsimran hangs back to jab it down into the off-side. Harboured thoughts of a single before turning down the idea
Boult to Prabhsimran, no run, on a length, angles in, Prabhsimran gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it down into the deck
KM Asif to Dhawan, no run, slants away from the southpaw after landing on a length. Dhawan looks to throw his willow at that one and misses. No movement on that one
KM Asif to Dhawan, 2 runs, plays it late and punches it square of the wicket. Little slip from the fielder trying to fetch it back and they get a brace. Was sweetly timed
KM Asif to Dhawan, no run, and drives on the up! Firm shot. That was hit on top of the bounce and the man at mid-off cut it off
Look at RR line up - all the match winners and world class players. Destructive batting and experienced bowling and lucky Indian talent.

KM Asif to Dhawan, 1 run, curtails his flash at a wide one a little and mistimes it wide of mid-off for a single. Was a slower length delivery well wide outside off and the batter just couldn't time it

KM Asif to Prabhsimran, , pick up and drop facility dished out by Prabhsimran like no one else. Was a length delivery on the pads, Prabhsimran got inside the line of the delivery and picked it off the pads to deposit it over deep backward square

KM Asif to Prabhsimran, , pick up and drop facility dished out by Prabhsimran like no one else. Was a length delivery on the pads, Prabhsimran got inside the line of the delivery and picked it off the pads to deposit it over deep backward square
KM Asif to Prabhsimran, no run, and some sort of respectability offered to the bowler as he stamps a back of a length delivery down into the deck. Played it late and under his nose
Boult to Dhawan, no run, little bit of angle into the batter and has been stabbed down into the off-side off the shoulder off the blade
Boult to Dhawan, , some superb timing from the skipper! Angles in from a length, Dhawan takes it from the sticks and whips the delivery down to square leg for a four

Boult to Dhawan, , a flat deck and Dhawan is relishing even on good balls. A short of a length delivery outside off, Dhawan hangs back and punches it to thread the ball between cover point and point for a four. Boult unable to find any movement off the deck or in the air
Boult to Dhawan, no run, and punches it again but this time the man at cover point dives to stop it
Boult to Dhawan, 1 run, slashes and takes the aerial route. Gets the ball down to third man on a bounce. Would be disappointed as he missed out there
Boult to Prabhsimran, 1 run, back of a length delivery, outside off, Prabhsimran guides the ball down to deep third man for a single. The slips were taken away before this ball
Dhawan looks in ominous touch.
KM Asif to Prabhsimran, , that's slapped! Dances down, KM Asif digs it in but he gets the freedom to slap it over mid-off. Punjab mean business
KM Asif to Prabhsimran, no run, banged in short, the ball takes off and Samson fumbles behind the sticks before recovering in time. That was a good effort ball
KM Asif to Prabhsimran, , wow! That was a very good ball. Banged in, cramped for room. Prabhsimran hopped up and just steered the ball close to his body to get it past point and third man for a four
Expect a RUN FEST today!

KM Asif to Prabhsimran, , you don't want to be soothsayer while watching this game! He was waiting for this short ball and then just dismissed it over deep square for a sixer. Massive hit indeed. Got hold of the delivery and sent it well over the fence

KM Asif to Prabhsimran, no run, and better from KM Asif as he pitched it up a little. Prabhsimran was again hanging back and mistimes the length delivery back to the bowler. Looked to flay it away sans much feet movement
KM Asif to Prabhsimran, , short, wide, Prabhsimran looks to hop up and slash it but misses
KM Asif to Prabhsimran, , chips down the track, gets to the landing of the ball and smashes it past the dive of the man at cover for a four
Ashwin to Dhawan, 1 run, dances down and heaves it down to deep mid for a single.
Ashwin to Prabhsimran, , fifty for this dynamic new duo at the top for Punjab. Prabhsimran sits down, takes on the tossed up delivery and slog sweeps it past the man at deep mid for a four

Ashwin to Prabhsimran, , and he is taking on Ashwin. Waits for the tossed up delivery, gets under it and lifts it over mid-off for a four. Just landed short of the long-off fence. Prabhsimran has started off brilliantly

Ashwin to Prabhsimran, , and he is taking on Ashwin. Waits for the tossed up delivery, gets under it and lifts it over mid-off for a four. Just landed short of the long-off fence. Prabhsimran has started off brilliantly
Ashwin to Prabhsimran, , walks across, goes for the slog sweep and misses. Has been wided as it was down leg
The ball seems to be wet. Ain't going to be easy.
Ashwin to Prabhsimran, 1 run, flatter one, outside off, Prabhsimran punches it down to long-on for a single
Ashwin to Dhawan, no run, chops a flatter down and finds the man at short third man

Ashwin to Dhawan, no run, flatter one, fuller one, evokes 'super ma, super ma' comments from the skipper as Dhawan jammed it down to cover. A quiet end to the over which started off on a good note for Punjab
This is good batting from Prabhsimran Singh. Another Indian player starting to make his mark on the big stage!! Wow, Exciting!!
Holder to Prabhsimran, no run, slower short ball, Prabhsimran was hanging back and looking to use the pace on the ball but got none or less of it and was beaten. Samson thought of an appeal
Holder to Prabhsimran, , goes full, wide, outside off, Prabhsimran gets under the ball and almost slices it over cover. Pretty much some smart powerplay batting by Prabhsimran
Holder to Prabhsimran, no run, resorts to the yorker and has been jammed down to the man at mid-wicket. That was angled in and Prabhsimran failed to get under it

Holder to Prabhsimran, 1 run, jumps down, flat bats the pull with almost one hand and Jaiswal at deep square does well to stop it. Only a single. The batter lost control of his bottom hand but still did well to infuse enough power into the shot
No target is safe here for Punjab with the batting line up that RR has. At no point should they put their foot down the peddle.
Holder to Dhawan, 1 run, charges down, banged in short, Dhawan mistimes the pull wide of long-on for a single

Holder to Prabhsimran, 1 run, tipped over the bar! A goalkeeper would have been proud of it but not Padikkal. That was a widish length ball and Prabhsimran ended up slicing the hit. The ball swirled in the air and Padikkal in a way overran it and lost balance when he was trying to clutch that one out of thin air. The ball hit his hands and went away

Ufff! Has been some action packed stuff so far. This guy Prabhsimran is trying to hit almost every ball and has done well so far. In most of the shots he has played, he has managed to retain his balance and hence the ball has travelled. Dhawan has done his bit as well.
Ashwin to Prabhsimran, 1 run, carrom ball at the sticks, worked away on to the on-side for a single. Thought of a second but get only one
Ashwin to Dhawan, no run, backs away, exposes his sticks, chops the ball down to point
Ashwin to Dhawan, 1 run, looks to chop that by backing away and inside edges it past and over the keeper for a single
Ashwin to Prabhsimran, 1 run, and manages to get behind the line of the ball with that firm push for a single. Was another carrom ball by Ashwin
Ashwin to Dhawan, 1 run, dances down a little, looks to heave it but gets it down to long-off for a single
Ashwin to Dhawan, 1 run, dances down a little, looks to heave it but gets it down to long-off for a single

The season has just began like a week back and we already have a few contenders for the emerging player award... Prabhsimran, Sai Sudarshan, Tilak Verma..
Indian Talent making their mark on the biggest stage

Ashwin to Prabhsimran, 1 run, flatter one, quicker one, Prabhsimran goes back and nudges the ball down past the bowler for a single. For a moment I thought there would be a dive from Ashwin but the ball managed to dribble away from him
Chahal to Prabhsimran, no run, well tossed up delivery, driven firmly back to the bowler. Good start for Chahal
Chahal to Prabhsimran, 2 runs, slower, shorter, Prabhsimran waits on it and chops the ball past point to race back for a brace.He has set the platform for Punjab tonight
Chahal to Prabhsimran, 1 run, well tossed up delivery, biffed down to long-on for a single
Chahal to Dhawan, no run, too full, Dhawan looks to heave it away on to the on-side and fails to time it
Chahal to Dhawan, , dances down the track to a floaty ball outside off and gets an outside edge. The ball went off the edge and fine for a four. Was beaten in flight but got away with it

Chahal to Dhawan, 2 runs, sits deep in his crease and muscles it over the bowler's head for a couple of runs. Parag at long-on does well to cut it off. Now Dhawan has decided to open his shoulders a little
Prabhsimran has been phenomenal so far. He has timed them really well. Yes, it is a good wicket. But Prabhsimran has managed to time his big shots really well.

Boult to Prabhsimran, , wow! Flat-batted over the bowler's head for a sixer. A short ball, sits up and Prabhsimran smashes it down the ground. Again a stable base, doesn't hurry into the shot and infuses enough power into the shot to get enough distance on the shot
Boult has run down to the long-on region and sorting a few issues near the sight-screen.
Boult to Prabhsimran, 1 run, goes round the wicket and angles in a slower ball for it to be tucked down to long-on for a single
Boult to Dhawan, 1 run, length delivery outside off and has been patted down into the off-side for a single. Clever thing to do as Boult has been brought back to bargain a wicket
Boult to Prabhsimran, 1 run, backs away and then just stabs it down into the off-side for a single
Boult to Dhawan, no run, right up there and has been jammed out into the off-side. That tailed in a little
Boult to Dhawan, no run, comes down the track and gets too close to the landing of the ball. Jams it down into the off-side to find cover
Holder to Prabhsimran, 1 run, bludgeons a fuller ball down to long-off for a single. Failed to get under it
Holder to Prabhsimran, 1 run, bludgeons a fuller ball down to long-off for a single. Failed to get under it
Holder to Dhawan, 2 runs, walks across his sticks, finds a fuller ball and heaves it down to deep mid for a couple of runs. He does this time and again
Holder to Dhawan, 1 run, right up there from Holder and Dhawan drives it to cover for a single
Holder to Prabhsimran,  Caught!!

Holder to Prabhsimran,  Caught by Buttler!! Buttler plucks out a terrific catch! It had to be an excellent piece of effort to bring an end to this wonderful innings. That was a short ball, Prabhsimran looked to slap it but ended up slicing it. The ball went aerial and the man from long-off ran in, covered some good ground and then dived to get two hands to it. Credit to him to cover so much of ground in such quick time. That made the catch possible. The ball also didn't pop out despite the elbows thudding into the ground.
Holder to Rajapaksa, 1 run, clips a fuller delivery down to fine leg for a single
Holder to Dhawan, 1 run, chips down the track and pats the ball down into the off-side for a single to deep cover

Ashwin to Dhawan, no run, that was slapped back hard! Was a fuller ball, outside off, Dhawan stayed low to smash it back at his partner at the other end who just couldn't get out of the way. That was hit really hard and Rajapaksa didn't have much time to react. The physio having a look
And Rajapaksa is going off. He was hit in the forearm on his right hand. That was slammed really hard by Dhawan. Not great news for Punjab.
Ashwin to Dhawan, 1 run, sits down and slashes one past point for a single. Didn't time it

Ashwin to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, flatter one, at the sticks, Jitesh Sharma tucks that off the pads and sends it to deep square for a single. Jitesh Sharma was pushing for a second but Dhawan wasn't interested
Ashwin to Dhawan, no run, jams the ball down into the off-side
Pitch looks great! Time for Dhawan to up that strike rate. Looking at RR batting line up, anything below 200 will be chased.
Ashwin to Dhawan, 1 run, flights one outside off and has been slog swept down to long-on for a single
Ashwin to Jitesh Sharma, no run, flatter one, Jitesh Sharma punches it off the front foot and sends it back to the bowler
Chahal to Dhawan, 1 run, well aired up delivery, slammed down to long-on for a single. Again couldn't time it as well as he could have

Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, 2 runs, charges down the track and inner-halves the ball wide of long-on for a couple of runs. Again tried to hit it a little too hard and hence the shot never got him the desired result
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, , drilled! Four. Was a fuller ball, outside off, Jitesh Sharma drove it past the dive of the man at cover for a four. Was a superb shot. The man at long-off had no chance
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, , drilled! Four. Was a fuller ball, outside off, Jitesh Sharma drove it past the dive of the man at cover for a four. Was a superb shot. The man at long-off had no chance

Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, , well well well! This man is continuing from where Prabhsimram left it. That was tossed up outside off, Jitesh Sharma got under the line to slam it over cover for a four. Well timed and placed
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, too full, drives it down to long-on for a single

Chahal to Dhawan, , for a second it looked as if he was beaten in flight. Chahal pushed it outside off and Dhawan jumped down a little too soon it seemed. But he managed to drag it powerfully and over long-on. Good muscular hit from the southpaw and that should give him some confidence to get going.
KM Asif to Jitesh Sharma, no run, tails in a very full ball, Jitesh Sharma looks to drive it and cue-ends the ball down into the deck
KM Asif to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, and fails to place it wide of mid-off. That was fuller, outside off, Jitesh Sharma cue-ends it down to mid-off. Single added to the tally

Impact player is a great improvisation. There are so many players looking for chances in IPL and were mostly used when some big names get injured. Now allowing 12 players in each game will give that opportunity to many uncapped players to showcase their talent.
KM Asif to Dhawan, 1 run, so far a good over from KM Asif as he nails another full ball. Dragged down to long-on for a single by Dhawan

KM Asif to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, moves across his sticks, looks to slog it and gets it down to deep square for a single. Padikkal initially thought it wouldn't spin but it did a little. He had it covered
KM Asif to Dhawan, , excellent from Dhawan! Waited on the length ball after walking across his sticks and then helped it over the short fine fielder for a four
Nothing for the bowler so far, especially for pace with the ball coming in straight lines. And easy for Prabhsimran to keep hitting through the line; which, he did with some panache.
KM Asif to Dhawan, , was a poor ball down leg, Dhawan looks to slog it across the line and misses. The keeper manages to glove it down to the man at short fine but they get the extra run
KM Asif to Jitesh Sharma, 2 runs, slants in a length delivery outside off and Jitesh Sharma looks to slog it but mistimes it down to deep mid for a couple of runs. That was good running by the duo

* A maiden IPL half-century for Prabhsimran Singh, came off 28 balls
* Prabhsimran continues on his merry ways, smashes Boult for a flat-batted six
* Holder gets rid of Prabhsimran; OUT for a 34-ball 60, excellent diving catch from Buttler
* Rajapaksha gets smashed above the wrist-band of his left hand after a powerful drive from Dhawan, is forced to retire hurt
*Jitesh Sharma gets going with a couple of lovely cover drives
*Chahal concedes 18 runs in the 12th over
Chahal to Dhawan, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, Dhawan laps it behind square on the on-side for a single
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, very full and sliding onto the right-hander, Jitesh can't get under it as he drives it to long-on for a single
Chahal to Dhawan, , , a low full-toss outside off - Dhawan bends down low and then rolls his wrists over the sweep, places it past square leg and beats Hetty, getting across from the deep
Chahal to Dhawan, , back-to-back boundaries for Dhawan, very full and on the leg-stump line, Dhawan clears his front-leg and whips it wide of mid-wicket, , he's pressing on after a slow start,

Chahal to Dhawan, 2 runs, a half-chance and , had to run back towards mid-on, was the wrong 'un and Dhawan was undone by the flight, had to reach out and got a massive top-edge - Chahal ran back, kept his eyes on the ball, but the ball was always dropping beyond him, gets his fingertips on the dive and fumbles
Chahal to Dhawan, ,  - Dhawan is in the mood now, flighted delivery on off, he stays leg-sided and then goes inside out over cover for a boundary, another expensive over from Chahal,
Boult, from round the wicket
Boult, from round the wicket
Boult to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, floaty slower ball, angling into the pads and it's heaved away to long-on for a single

Looks like the ball has gone out of shape, the two umpires have a look and . Dhawan has scored 26 off the last 8 balls he's faced, beginning to gain some real momentum, PBKS will be disappointed if rthey don't go past 200 from here
Boult to Dhawan, 1 run, banged in short and angling into the body, pulled down to long leg for a single, brings up the
Boult to Jitesh Sharma, , slapped, , slower short ball from Boult, but Jitesh latched onto the width and carved it cover for a 89m hit
Boult to Jitesh Sharma, 2 runs, on a good length and angling into the right-hander, dragged away to the right of long-on and Jitesh comes back for the second

Boult to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, a miscue, but Jitesh gets away with hit, Boult bowled one into the surface and got some extra bounce, hurried onto the right-hander who could only splice the pull, lobbed through the vacant cover-point region
Ruturaj, Shubman, Sudarshan, Badoni, Prabhsimran and many more to come
Boult to Dhawan, 1 run, very full and at the pads, flicked down to long leg for a single
Chahal to Dhawan, no run, Dhawan mises out on a full-toss, a pre-empted move to play the reverse sweep, and he finds backward point with the shot

Chahal to Dhawan, , he nails the reverse sweep now, backward point is in and this is a tempting option - gets down low and gets enough on the shot to clear the infield, couple of bounces and over the ropes
Chahal to Dhawan, 1 run, Chahal darts one full and down leg, flicked behind square on the on-side for a single
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma, , slower and wider from Chahal, but it's past the tramlines and is called as a wide
Chahal to Jitesh Sharma,  Caught!!

Chahal to Jitesh Sharma,  Caught by Riyan Parag!! Jitesh has found Parag to perfection at long-off, and the home crowd is thrilled to bits. Was a low full-toss as Jitesh jumped down the pitch, was looking to go inside out, but he couldn't completely under it, it meant that he couldn't get the necessary elevation on the shot, went straighter and down the throat of long-off, who moved across swiftly to his left.
Time for the . 26 balls remaining and PBKS are coasting towards a 200 score. A belter here in Guwahati and this could set-up an entertaining chase
Chahal to Raza, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, Raza works it down to long-on for a single
Chahal to Dhawan, no run, Dhawan attempts the reverse sweep once again, gets into an awkward position and under-edges it onto his pads
We've a impact player coming in.  for the Royals
We've a impact player coming in.  for the Royals
Ashwin to Raza,  Bowled!!

Ashwin to Raza,  Bowled!! Lovely, lovely stuff from Ashwin and the Royals have two in no time - was the carrom ball, drifted in with the angle and then went away with the angle, drew Raza forward and then straightened past the outside edge, crashing into the off-stump. Ashwin certainly enjoyed that and it's a no show from Raza tonight at the Barsapara.
Ashwin to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, flighted and drifting down leg, nudged towards short fine and they're off for a quick single
Ashwin to Dhawan, 1 run, Dhawan keeps playing the reverse sweep without much success, drags it off the inner half towards backward point for a single
Ashwin to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, Ashwin tosses one on the leg-stump line. worked behind square on the on-side for a single
Ashwin to Dhawan, 1 run, Ashwin slows down the pace and then drifts to down leg, Dhawan was coming down the pitch and heaves it behind square on the on-side for a single

Ashwin to Shahrukh Khan, 2 runs, good fielding from Parag, sprinted across to his left at long-on, dives and makes a fine stiop, saved a couple of runs- flighted delivery on off and was drilled down the ground by Shahrukh
Jason Holder to probably bowl the 18th and 20th over
Holder to Dhawan, 1 run, full and following Dhawan as he backed away, an inside edge onto the pad and rolls to the off-side for a single
Holder, from round the wicket
Holder to Shahrukh Khan, no run, yorker length delivery angling across the right-hander, Shahrukh looks to squeeze it down towards third man and missed

Holder to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, has Shahrukh been run-out at the bowler's end? He was trying to scramble home after driving straight to the fielder at cover. Hetmyer's throw is slightly wide and that gives him enough time to slide the bat in - NOT OUT is the call. Was a low full-toss from Holder

Holder to Dhawan, no run, Dhawan and his fascination with the reverse shots proving a waste here - slower short ball and he was in no position on the shot, tried to swat it away and is undone by the bounce

Holder to Dhawan, , , he gets one reverse lap away, the timing is sweet and it sails over the ropes for a maximum - Holder saw it coming and bowled full and at the pads, somehow Dhawan got his bat down in time and scooped it over backward point
Holder to Dhawan, 1 run, low full-toss on the pads, whipped down to long leg for a single

KM Asif to Dhawan, , Asif goes full and wide of off as Dhawan pre-empted the shuffle across the off-stump, looks to drive and misses, isn't called as a wide and  - it did go past the tramlines, but Dhawan was a long way across as well. It actually didn't land on the pitch, the ball was close to the bat, but UltraEdge has a flat line. Not sure this can be given as a wide, it has just gone past the bat, but it hasn't landed at all, and so will be called as a wide. Good spot by Shahrukh Khan who asked his partner to review

KM Asif to Dhawan, , Asif goes full and wide of off as Dhawan pre-empted the shuffle across the off-stump, looks to drive and misses, isn't called as a wide and  - it did go past the tramlines, but Dhawan was a long way across as well. It actually didn't land on the pitch, the ball was close to the bat, but UltraEdge has a flat line. Not sure this can be given as a wide, it has just gone past the bat, but it hasn't landed at all, and so will be called as a wide. Good spot by Shahrukh Khan who asked his partner to review
KM Asif to Dhawan, , , on a good length and at the stumps, Dhawan shuffles across, used the pace on the ball and laps it fine, sails over the ropes for a maximum

KM Asif to Dhawan, 1 run, , this was destined to the boundary, but he threw himself at the ball and saved three runs for his team - length ball outside off and Dhawan hammered the drive back past the non-striker, was racing away past mid-off until Parag's intervention

In such a belter of a wicket, after going for back to back fours in the first few balls, finishing with 1/25 from 4 overs is an excellent achievement. Ashwin the T20 bowler needs to be given the due respect.
KM Asif to Shahrukh Khan, , byes, 1 run, that's a wild wild delivery - high full-toss down leg, Samson throws himself and makes a half-top, but it's a no-ball for height -
KM Asif to Dhawan, , , Dhawan is making up for lost time, wide full-toss and he carves it over extra-cover, almost went all the way, bounced right in front of the ropes

KM Asif to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, a near perfect yorker, right at the blockhole, squeezed away behind square on the on-side for a single

Holder to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, on a good length and at the stumps, Shahrukh shuffles right across and heaves it to deep mid-wicket for a single

Shahrukh is standing right in front of his stumps
Holder to Shahrukh Khan,  Caught!!

Holder to Shahrukh Khan,  Caught by Buttler!! Holder has his second and it's yet another smart catch from Buttler, running in from long-on - was very full and angling across the right-hander, Shahrukh didn't have the room to get under it, scooped it in the air and towards long-on, the ball seemed to be dropping safely, but Buttler ran in, slid forward and then took a good two-handed catch, right in front of his boot lace.
Holder to Sam Curran, no run, yorker length delivery and angling into the left-hander, Curran backs away and squeezes it back at the bowler
Holder to Sam Curran, 1 run, , fuller length delivery at the stumps, driven down to long-on for a single

The Royals will be pretty happy with this chase. Samson can be seen walking away without looking too worried. The pitch is flat, some boundaries are short and the dew will play a part, it could only get worse and that would mean batting becoming easier as the ball skids through in the 2nd innings. Prabhsimran gave PBS a rollicking start, but his captain got stuck. While Prabhsimran smashed a fine 34-ball 60, Dhawan at one point was on 30 off 30. He did get better as his innings progressed, Rajapaksa was unfortunate to be forced to retire hurt, Jitesh played a nice little cameo, but PBKS didn't get the finish they'd have wanted. Ravi Ashwin and Holder were outstanding while the others went for a few. RR's batting is loaded with Holder set to bat at 9 and they'll fancy chasing this down. Back shortly for their reply..

Back for the chase and there's a change in RR's batting order. . Murali Kartik says on air that Buttler went off the field immediately after taking that catch in the last over - Sam Curran to start for PBKS, a slip in place

Sam Curran to Jaiswal, , .. and Jaiswal is off and running in some style, fraction short by Curran and he's quick to swivel across, picked the length early and shovelled it into the stands over square leg, that's some start from the youngster
Coming back to Buttler, looks like he injured his finger while taking the catch that dismissed Shahrukh. RR would hope it's nothing serious. The good thing is he's padded up in the dug-out
Sam Curran to Jaiswal, no run, fuller length delivery on off, Jaiswal leans forward and finds mid-off with the drive
Sam Curran to Jaiswal, no run, on a good length and just outside off - Jaiswal shuffles across and finds mid-on with the on-drive
Sam Curran to Jaiswal, no run, fuller length delivery on off, Jaiswal leans well forward and finds mid-off with the drive
Sam Curran to Jaiswal, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, chopped away behind square on the off-side for a single
Sam Curran to Jaiswal, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, chopped away behind square on the off-side for a single
Sam Curran to Ashwin, no run, on a good length and angling across the right-hander, Ashwin's feet is rooted to the crease as he frails at that and missed
Arshdeep, from the other end, a slip in place
Arshdeep Singh to Jaiswal, , , short of a good length and just outside off, was an off-pace delivery, but with width on offer, Jaiswal could wait on it and crash it square past point for a boundary

Catching practice at extra-cover, on a good length and well wide of off, Jaiswal leant into the drive, was slightly early into the shot and ended it hitting it straight into the hands of Short at extra-cover - the substitute fielder's first impact on #IPL2023 and the in-form Jaiswal has been dismissed.

Ashwin & Buttler batting together. From the run out at the non-striker end a few seasons ago to this, IPL is truly a great event.

Sam Curran to Buttler, 2 runs, a chance and , the ball is following him, but he'd reckon he should have taken it, did all the hard work, got across to the ball at a good height, but as he fell down, the ball popped out of his grasp, short of a good length and angling across the right-hander - Buttler was in no control over the pull and the ball lobbed over square leg, big big chance that's missed by the Kings

Arshdeep Singh to Ashwin,  Caught by Dhawan!! A duck for Ashwin and the experiment has ended in failure - hard length causing his downfall, banged in short and it kept riding onto the right-hander, cramped for room on the pull, all that Ashwin could manage was a big top-edge, lobbed high and over mid-on. Dhawan kept back-pedalling, got into a good position and held on, before starting his thigh-slap celebrations. RR have lost their opener and now their make-shift opener as well.

Punjab Vs RR produced some of the best matches, ready for once more.

Nathan Ellis to Samson, , , exqsuite timing from Samson - on a good length and well outside off, he leans across, lets the basll come, opens the face of the bat and then deftly drives it backward of square on the off-side for another boundary

Ellis has got the big wicket and he's chuffed to bits, so good from the Australian bowler - very full and at the stumps, Buttler was looking to play the on-drive, the bat turned slightly on impact and the ball popped up off the pad, Ellis was quick on the followthrough, runs forward, dives and completes a good two-handed catch, pivotal moment of the match.

The game is nicely poised here. Punjab are slightly ahead at the moment, but anything around 60-70 (in the last 5 overs) looks pretty chaseable on this surface. Where's your money going? Do let us know via I0$ section on the site...

That's the problem of relying too much on top order. RR's middle order is really poor. After Jaiswal, Sanju and Buttler, there is not much batting down the order apart from Hetmyer. Devdutt is playing at wrong number and is often a slow starter, and Riyan hasn't utilised the chances so far. 'A chance for all of them to come good tonight'
Paddikal needs to prove his mettle for RR. After the stellar season with RCB, he has not have had a big impact or a match winning knock.

*Samson looks to take on Chahar who comes into the attack.
*Raza starts on an expensive note.
* Ellis traps the big fish. Samson goes for 42. Advantage Punjab going into the last lap.

Phewf! What a game. It was very clear from the onset that anything under 200 would be really tough to defend, and it did get really tight towards the end. Yes, there was that Dhruv Jurel magic, but the Royals never really looked out of the contest. There could be questions about Ashwin's promotion and the non-boundary overs from 8-11, and of course the struggles of Padikkal. Despite all of that, they threatened to steal the game thanks to a 22 year-old superstar Dhruv Jurel. The impact player not only proved his worth in his first-ever outing of the IPL, but displayed his range and fierce attitude during his 15-ball 32. All said and done, Nathan Ellis deserves a huge chunk of credit for Punjab's victory. He bowled at crucial stages of the game and picked up important wickets to draw the game in his side's favour. On a day which saw the bowlers travel frequently, Ellis picked up 4 and just conceded 30 off his 4 overs. Bonzer!! Post-match reactions imminent, stick around...

- To be honest, it was a very good track to bat on, not much movement with the new ball and they batted really well, had the momentum in the powerplay. Our bowlers used the variations on a high-scoring wicket and I thought we did well to restrict them to 197. Jos wasn't fully fit (injured his finger while taking the catch), the thinking behind keeping Padikkal (in the middle order) was to tackle their two spinners in the middle overs. The coaches have put a lot of work behind him (on Dhruv Jurel), we had a work week camp before the IPL, but the way they have worked a lot of time in our academies (during off-season), having faced 1000s of balls and I'm happy with the way they're progressing. I was expecting the dew to come in the second innings, but it was evident that it was there right at the start, need to be prepared better for such things in the next game.

I think when it comes to this situations, it is do or die. If you know the yorker, you got to use it. Some days it would work and some days it won’t. They changed their ball during the end of their innings. But we weren’t able to. I was with Prabhsimran four years back with Punjab. Happy to sit in the dug out when it comes to batting. All that matters is we won. Amazingly hard to bowl with the wet ball. It is incredibly hard to hold the seam. It is naturally hard to bowl a yorker with a cross seam.

There were some nervous moments, I was trying to keep my calm and discussing plans with my bowlers. Was happy with the score we put up. We scoring 197 and my bowlers giving those early wickets and then Nathan came in and bowled supebly. It was a full team effort. These 2 games we got a great start, Prabh did really well and I tried my best to increase my strike-rate. We want to keep the momentum going as we got a good batting line-up. We respect the opponents' bowlers but want to keep the intent and aggression going.

Just stoked to get the win, pleased to get some awards but from a team's point of view nice to get that win. In T20 every ball counts, staying in the moment is really the key. When I was bowling in the backend, I was trying to get my variations right and calculate what the best ball is at that time. For me it's cross-seam and it worked out really well tonight

That's a wrap of game 8 then. It's been the day of two 22 year-old keeper-bats. Prabhsimran Singh and Dhruv Jurel. While one kickstarted the contest with an array of fearless strokes, the other exhibited effervescent attitude through his shot-slection on his maiden IPL game. A near-perfect IPL recipe, if one can put it that way. Whose turn will it be tonight? Join us for the clash between KKR and RCB from the Eden Gardens in a few hours' time. Until then, cheers and goodbye from I0$, I1$ and I2$.
